cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object counting in images using convolutional neural networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new approach to reduce overfitting in training one-look regression models. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses deep learning techniques to solve a computer vision problem. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to the backend of a convolutional neural network. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with counting objects in images, which is a multimedia-related task.
